adDSUIQPassword.name: adDSUIQPassword
adDSUIQPassword.description: Sets the Telnet and Vt100 Terminal Control Password (10 characters maximum).

adDSUIQTOD.name: adDSUIQTOD
adDSUIQTOD.description: Sets the Time of Day with the format hh:mm.

adDSUIQDate.name: adDSUIQDate
adDSUIQDate.description: Sets the Date with format MM-DD-YY.

adDSUIQGatewayIpAddress.name: adDSUIQGatewayIpAddress
adDSUIQGatewayIpAddress.description: Sets the Network's Gateway IP Address.

adDSUIQTrapManagerIpAddress.name: adDSUIQTrapManagerIpAddress
adDSUIQTrapManagerIpAddress.description: Sets the IP Address of the Trap Host Manager.

adDSUIQTrapManagerDLCI.name: adDSUIQTrapManagerDLCI
adDSUIQTrapManagerDLCI.description: Sets the DLCI of the Trap Host Manager. (Range 16 - 1007).

adDSUIQControPortBaud.name: adDSUIQControPortBaud
adDSUIQControPortBaud.description: Selects the Control Port baud rate.

adDSUIQAlarmState.name: adDSUIQAlarmState
adDSUIQAlarmState.description: This bit map variable indicates alarm conditions which are currently set. When an alarm condition occurs, the corresponding event bit is set in this variable. If armed, setting the event will generate an Alarm Trap. The various alarm event bit positions are: 1 = Network physical link up. 2 = Network physical link down. 4 = Network signal state up. 8 = Network signal state down.

adDSUIQArmAlarm.name: adDSUIQArmAlarm
adDSUIQArmAlarm.description: This bit map variable arms or disarms an individual or group of events identified in adFradAlarmState as a source for generation of an Alarm Trap. The various arm event bit positions are : 1 = Network physical link up. 2 = Network physical link down. 4 = Network signal state up. 8 = Network signal state down.

adDSUIQAbortConfig.name: adDSUIQAbortConfig
adDSUIQAbortConfig.description: A Set will cancel the current selections and revert to the last Saved configuration.

adDSUIQSaveConfig.name: adDSUIQSaveConfig
adDSUIQSaveConfig.description: A Set operation will reset the unit and save current selections.

adDSUIQNetPortLoopRate.name: adDSUIQNetPortLoopRate
adDSUIQNetPortLoopRate.description: Selects the Rate for the DDS interface.

adDSUIQNetPortClockSource.name: adDSUIQNetPortClockSource
adDSUIQNetPortClockSource.description: Selects the Timing source for the DDS interface.

adDSUIQNetPortSignaling.name: adDSUIQNetPortSignaling
adDSUIQNetPortSignaling.description: Signaling type for the frame relay management interface.

adDSUIQNetPortt391.name: adDSUIQNetPortt391
adDSUIQNetPortt391.description: Sets the polling interval in seconds for the frame relay management interface. (Range 5 - 30).

adDSUIQNetPortn391.name: adDSUIQNetPortn391
adDSUIQNetPortn391.description: Sets the interval between full status polls for the frame relay management interface. (Range 1 - 255).

adDSUIQNetPortn392.name: adDSUIQNetPortn392
adDSUIQNetPortn392.description: Sets the error count for the frame relay management interface. (Range 1 - 10).

adDSUIQNetPortn393.name: adDSUIQNetPortn393
adDSUIQNetPortn393.description: Sets the error window (number of polling events)for the frame relay management interface. (Range 1 - 10).

adDSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci1Mode.name: adDSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci1Mode
adDSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci1Mode.description: Sets the mode for the managent DLCI 1. If set for shared, management DLCI 1 is used for customer data and IQ management data. If set for dedicated, management DLCI 1 is used only for IQ management data and is not passed to the attached frame relay DTE device.

adDSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci2Mode.name: adDSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci2Mode
adDSUIQNetPortMgmtDlci2Mode.description: Sets the mode for the managent DLCI 2. If set for shared, management DLCI 2 is used for customer data and IQ management data. If set for dedicated, management DLCI 2 is used only for IQ management data and is not passed to the attached frame relay DTE device.

adDSUIQNetMgmtDlci1.name: adDSUIQNetMgmtDlci1
adDSUIQNetMgmtDlci1.description: Sets the DLCI for management PVC 1. (Range 16 - 1007).

adDSUIQNetMgmtDlci2.name: adDSUIQNetMgmtDlci2
adDSUIQNetMgmtDlci2.description: Sets the DLCI for management PVC 2. (Range 16 - 1007).

adDSUIQNetPortMaxPVCs.name: adDSUIQNetPortMaxPVCs
adDSUIQNetPortMaxPVCs.description: Sets the maxium PVCs supported by the IQ unit. (Range 1 - 100).

adDSUIQNetPortHistIntervals.name: adDSUIQNetPortHistIntervals
adDSUIQNetPortHistIntervals.description: Sets the number of history intervals for storage.

adDSUIQNetPortHistIntervalsAvailable.name: adDSUIQNetPortHistIntervalsAvailable
adDSUIQNetPortHistIntervalsAvailable.description: Returns the number of history intervals allowed based on the maxium number of PVCs selected.

adDSUIQDtePortInterface.name: adDSUIQDtePortInterface
adDSUIQDtePortInterface.description: Selects the DTE Port Interface type.

adDSUIQDteCTSOption.name: adDSUIQDteCTSOption
adDSUIQDteCTSOption.description: Selects the Clear to Send (CTS) option.

adDSUIQDteDSROption.name: adDSUIQDteDSROption
adDSUIQDteDSROption.description: Selects the Data Set Ready (DSR) option.

adDSUIQDtePortMgmtDLCI.name: adDSUIQDtePortMgmtDLCI
adDSUIQDtePortMgmtDLCI.description: Sets the DTE Port Management DLCI. (Range 16 - 1007).

adDSUIQDtePortt392.name: adDSUIQDtePortt392
adDSUIQDtePortt392.description: Sets the timeout in seconds between polling intervals. (Range 5 - 30).

adDSUIQDtePortn392.name: adDSUIQDtePortn392
adDSUIQDtePortn392.description: Sets the number of error events for the frame relay management. (Range 1 - 10).

adDSUIQDtePortn393.name: adDSUIQDtePortn393
adDSUIQDtePortn393.description: Sets the error window (polling events) for the frame relay management (Range 1 - 10).

adDSUIQDteManagementPvcOption.name: adDSUIQDteManagementPvcOption
adDSUIQDteManagementPvcOption.description: Controls the presence of the DTE management PVC in a full status response to the DTE device.

adDSUIQDteSignalingResponsesOption.name: adDSUIQDteSignalingResponsesOption
adDSUIQDteSignalingResponsesOption.description: Determines how the IQ device will respond to polls from the DTE device during a network failure. If set to always on, the IQ will respond to polls during a network failure. If set to follow network, the IQ will not respond thus emulating a failure to the DTE device. If the IQ is responsible for dial backup, this option should be set to always on.

adDSUIQDteFlowControlOption.name: adDSUIQDteFlowControlOption
adDSUIQDteFlowControlOption.description: Determines how the IQ device will respond to congestion during DBU operation. If set for none, the IQ will drop frames during DBU operation when severe congestion occurs. If set for hardware, the IQ will vary the DTE TC clock in order to control the amount of data offered to the IQ when severe congestion occurs. FECN/BECN mode will set the FECN bit in outbound frames and set BECN bit for inbound frames leaving flow control up to the DTE devices.

adDSUIQPvcCIR.name: adDSUIQPvcCIR
adDSUIQPvcCIR.description: Commited Information Rate for this PVC in Kbps.

adDSUIQPvcSequenceOption.name: adDSUIQPvcSequenceOption
adDSUIQPvcSequenceOption.description: Sequence number allows the IQ to detect lost frames across the frame relay service. This option should be disabled for PVCs that do not have IQ on both ends.

adDSUIQPvcDelayPacketOption.name: adDSUIQPvcDelayPacketOption
adDSUIQPvcDelayPacketOption.description: Delay packet option for this PVC allows the IQ to sample round trip delay across the frame relay service. This option should be disabled for PVCs that do not have IQ on both ends.

adDSUIQPvcDBUDLCI.name: adDSUIQPvcDBUDLCI
adDSUIQPvcDBUDLCI.description: Used when this PVC entry is used for dial backup. This value should contain the PVC address as seen on the far end of the PVC.

adDSUIQPvcStatsControl.name: adDSUIQPvcStatsControl
adDSUIQPvcStatsControl.description: Stats Control option determines how the IQ will track statistics for this PVC entry. Auto will allow the IQ to track statistics for a PVC if enough memory is available.

adDSUIQDDSState.name: adDSUIQDDSState
adDSUIQDDSState.description: Current status of the DDS interface

adDSUIQDteControlLeads.name: adDSUIQDteControlLeads
adDSUIQDteControlLeads.description: This bit map integer reflects the current state of the DTE control leads as follows: bit meaning 0 CTS 1 RTS 2 DSR 3 DTR 4 DCD A 1 means the lead is on.

adDSUIQDBUPortType.name: adDSUIQDBUPortType
adDSUIQDBUPortType.description: Returns the DBU card type installed.

adDSUIQLANPortStatus.name: adDSUIQLANPortStatus
adDSUIQLANPortStatus.description: Returns the LAN card type installed.

adDSUIQLEDstatus.name: adDSUIQLEDstatus
adDSUIQLEDstatus.description: This bit map integer reflects DSUIQ front panel LED state as follows: bit meaning 0 TEST 1 ALARM 2 DCD 3 RD 4 TD 5 CTS 6 RTS

adDSUIQDTESignalingState.name: adDSUIQDTESignalingState
adDSUIQDTESignalingState.description: Current state of the PVC signaling between the DSUIQ and the attached frame relay dte.

adDSUIQNETSignalingState.name: adDSUIQNETSignalingState
adDSUIQNETSignalingState.description: Current state of the PVC signaling between the DSUIQ and the frame relay service.

adDSUIQNETPVCConfigTableSize.name: adDSUIQNETPVCConfigTableSize
adDSUIQNETPVCConfigTableSize.description: Current count of rows in the PVC config table.

adDSUIQDBUState.name: adDSUIQDBUState
adDSUIQDBUState.description: Current state of the DBU interface.

adDSUIQIntDDSUnavailableTime.name: adDSUIQIntDDSUnavailableTime
adDSUIQIntDDSUnavailableTime.description: Amount of time in seconds the DDS port is unavailable due to test or in an inactive state.

adDSUIQIntDDSStateChange.name: adDSUIQIntDDSStateChange
adDSUIQIntDDSStateChange.description: Number of changes in the DDS port state. This includes all normal, inactive, and test state transitions.

adDSUIQIntDDSBPVFrameError.name: adDSUIQIntDDSBPVFrameError
adDSUIQIntDDSBPVFrameError.description: Number of BPVs received when the DDS is set for 56K mode or the number of DDS framing errors when the DDS is set for 64K mode.

adDSUIQDayDDSUnavailableTime.name: adDSUIQDayDDSUnavailableTime
adDSUIQDayDDSUnavailableTime.description: Amount of time in seconds the DDS port is unavailable due to test or in an inactive state.

adDSUIQDayDDSStateChange.name: adDSUIQDayDDSStateChange
adDSUIQDayDDSStateChange.description: Number of changes in the DDS port state. This includes all normal, inactive, and test state transitions.

adDSUIQDayDDSBPVFrameError.name: adDSUIQDayDDSBPVFrameError
adDSUIQDayDDSBPVFrameError.description: Number of BPVs received when the DDS is set for 56K mode or the number of DDS framing errors when the DDS is set for 64K mode.

adDSUIQDiagnosticDlci.name: adDSUIQDiagnosticDlci
adDSUIQDiagnosticDlci.description: Sets the DLCI for PVC Loopback. (Range 16 - 1007).

adDSUIQDiagnosticControl.name: adDSUIQDiagnosticControl
adDSUIQDiagnosticControl.description: Starts or Stops PVC Loopback Test.

adDSUIQDiagnosticDuration.name: adDSUIQDiagnosticDuration
adDSUIQDiagnosticDuration.description: Sets the Length of the PVC Loopback in minutes.

adDSUIQDiagnosticSecondsRemaining.name: adDSUIQDiagnosticSecondsRemaining
adDSUIQDiagnosticSecondsRemaining.description: PVC Loopback Test time remaining in seconds.

adDSUIQDBUOption.name: adDSUIQDBUOption
adDSUIQDBUOption.description: This option specifies whether the unit automatically enters dial backup mode or waits for manual setup.

adDSUIQDBUStartLockout.name: adDSUIQDBUStartLockout
adDSUIQDBUStartLockout.description: This option selects the hour to begin disabling dial backup operation when daily or weekend lockout mode is active.

adDSUIQDBUEndLockout.name: adDSUIQDBUEndLockout
adDSUIQDBUEndLockout.description: This option selects the hour to end dial backup lockout when daily or weekend lockout mode is active.

adDSUIQDBUMode.name: adDSUIQDBUMode
adDSUIQDBUMode.description: This option specifies the dial backup operating mode for the unit as orginate or answer. One end must be set to originate and the other end to answer.

adDSUIQDBUOOS.name: adDSUIQDBUOOS
adDSUIQDBUOOS.description: This option enables the unit to enter backup mode if an out-of-service condition is detected from the network.

adDSUIQDBUNoRx.name: adDSUIQDBUNoRx
adDSUIQDBUNoRx.description: This option enables the unit to enter backup mode when a loss of receive signal is detected from the network.

adDSUIQDBUNoSealCurr.name: adDSUIQDBUNoSealCurr
adDSUIQDBUNoSealCurr.description: This option enables the unit to enter backup mode when a loss of sealing current is detected from the network.

adDSUIQDBUNoLMI.name: adDSUIQDBUNoLMI
adDSUIQDBUNoLMI.description: This option enables the unit to enter backup mode when network PVC signaling state goes down.

adDSUIQAutoRestoreTimer.name: adDSUIQAutoRestoreTimer
adDSUIQAutoRestoreTimer.description: This option selects the amount of time that the DSUIQ circuit must be active before the unit switches from backup to normal mode of operation. The timer value is in minutes from 0 to 60. A zero value disables automatic restore, DSUIQ operation must be restored manually.

adDSUIQRedialCount.name: adDSUIQRedialCount
adDSUIQRedialCount.description: This option allows the selection of the number of times the unit will redial the Far End unit when attempting to go to backup and a busy or reorder condition occurs. Redial count can be set for a maximum of 60.

adDSUIQDBUFailTimeout.name: adDSUIQDBUFailTimeout
adDSUIQDBUFailTimeout.description: This option allows the selection of the amount of time that the dedicated circuit failure condition is active before attempting to enter dial backup mode. The Fail Timeout value is in increments of 10 seconds up to a maximum of 600 seconds.

adDSUIQDBURedialTimer.name: adDSUIQDBURedialTimer
adDSUIQDBURedialTimer.description: This option works in conjunction with the Redial Counter option. The Redial Timer specifies the amount of time between redial attempts. The Redial Timer value is seconds, up to a maximum of 60 seconds.

adDSUIQDBUPassCheck.name: adDSUIQDBUPassCheck
adDSUIQDBUPassCheck.description: This option allows the unit to send and verify a dial backup passcode for an additional level of security. When enabled, the originate unit sends the passcode and the answer unit checks the passcode before the backup connection is considered valid.

adDSUIQDBUPassCode.name: adDSUIQDBUPassCode
adDSUIQDBUPassCode.description: This option sets the dial backup passcode used to provide an additional level of security. A passcode of one to ten digit characters can be set. If enabled, the originate unit sends the passcode and the answer unit checks the passcode to verify the connection.

adDSUIQWeekendLockout.name: adDSUIQWeekendLockout
adDSUIQWeekendLockout.description: This option enables or disables Weekend Lockout for Dial Backup operation. If enabled, no backup will occur from midnight Friday to midnight Sunday.

adDSUIQDailyLockout.name: adDSUIQDailyLockout
adDSUIQDailyLockout.description: This option enables or disables Daily Lockout for Dial Backup operation. If enabled, no backup will occur between Lockout Start hour and Lockout End hour.

adDSUIQAnswerAlways.name: adDSUIQAnswerAlways
adDSUIQAnswerAlways.description: This option enables or disables Answer Always for Dial Backup operation. If enabled, the answer unit answers any incoming call regardless of failed conditions.

adDSUIQBeeperOption.name: adDSUIQBeeperOption
adDSUIQBeeperOption.description: This option enables or disables the audible alarm when the IQ unit goes into dial backup mode.

adDSUIQDBUPhoneNumber1.name: adDSUIQDBUPhoneNumber1
adDSUIQDBUPhoneNumber1.description: This option is used to set a phone number to place a DBU call.

adDSUIQDBUPhoneNumber2.description: This option is used to set a phone number to place a DBU call.

adDSUIQV34LineType.name: adDSUIQV34LineType
adDSUIQV34LineType.description: This option selects the type of analog phone line.

adDSUIQDCEInterfaceType.name: adDSUIQDCEInterfaceType
adDSUIQDCEInterfaceType.description: This option enables or disables Answer Always for Dial Backup operation. If enabled, the answer unit answers any incoming call regardless of failed conditions.

adDSUIQDCEBitRate.name: adDSUIQDCEBitRate
adDSUIQDCEBitRate.description: This option is uses for utilization measurement of the DBU port when an external DCE device is used. Set this parameter in KBPS close to the connection rate.
